WEBVTT

00:00.668 --> 00:02.701
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>
[ cadence crying ]

00:02.703 --> 00:03.702
Juliette?

00:03.704 --> 00:05.570
We're gonna find your mama.

00:05.572 --> 00:06.838
Photographer: Let's get you two
a little closer.

00:06.839 --> 00:08.105
Gunnar: You made your feelings
pretty clear --

00:08.107 --> 00:10.140
Not friends.
Barely bandmates.

00:10.142 --> 00:11.741
The truth is, I'm gay.

00:11.743 --> 00:13.593
[ reporters murmuring ]

00:13.594 --> 00:15.444
I'm sorry, son. I'm gonna
have to drop you from the label.

00:15.446 --> 00:17.262
You're going to prison,
teddy.

00:17.263 --> 00:19.079
Girl: You'd think they'd be
embarrassed to be out in public.

00:19.082 --> 00:20.714
Their dad's, like,
a total criminal.

00:20.716 --> 00:22.415
Beverly:
I heard you singing to me.

00:22.417 --> 00:24.750
I know
you haven't left my side.

00:24.752 --> 00:26.418
[ flatline ]
mama?

00:26.420 --> 00:28.019
[ rapid beeping ]

00:28.021 --> 00:29.086
Mama, wake up.

00:29.088 --> 00:38.695
Maddie:
¶ I wonder what it's like
to live on cloud nine ¶

00:38.697 --> 00:43.799
¶ where everything's fine ¶

00:43.801 --> 00:46.167
¶ all of the time ¶

00:47.703 --> 00:49.636
[ monitor beeping ]

00:49.638 --> 00:51.471
¶ I wonder how ¶

00:51.473 --> 00:52.505
This is for you.

00:52.507 --> 00:55.541
¶ it feels to be afraid ¶

00:55.543 --> 00:57.342
[ cellphone rings ]

00:57.344 --> 00:58.576
It's the girls' school.
I'm gonna grab this.

00:58.578 --> 00:59.577
All right. Take it.

00:59.579 --> 01:03.513
¶ day after day ¶

01:03.515 --> 01:07.149
¶ after it rains ¶

01:09.086 --> 01:14.722
¶ someday, somehow ¶

01:14.724 --> 01:18.225
¶ before too long ¶

01:18.227 --> 01:24.397
¶ I'll say goodbye
to my burdens ¶

01:24.399 --> 01:30.269
¶ I'll fly beyond the sun ¶

01:33.673 --> 01:38.474
¶ fly ¶

01:38.476 --> 01:42.210
¶ fly ¶

01:42.212 --> 01:45.613
¶ beyond the sun ¶

01:48.417 --> 01:52.818
¶ fly ¶

01:52.820 --> 01:56.687
¶ I'll fly ¶
[ beeping ]

01:56.689 --> 02:00.590
¶ beyond the sun ¶

02:03.094 --> 02:07.863
¶ someday, somehow ¶

02:07.865 --> 02:11.799
¶ before too long ¶

02:11.801 --> 02:17.837
¶ I'll say goodbye
to my burdens ¶

02:17.839 --> 02:27.512
¶ I'll fly beyond the sun ¶

02:27.514 --> 02:29.514
[ claps ]

02:29.516 --> 02:31.415
Wow, maddie.
That was fantastic.

02:31.417 --> 02:33.550
Thank you, mr. Sims. I didn't
know you were coming in today.

02:33.552 --> 02:35.118
I had to check on
my prized pupils.

02:35.120 --> 02:37.320
Or should I say "pupil."
where's daphne?

02:37.322 --> 02:40.289
Principal: Everyone agrees
she threw the first punch.

02:40.291 --> 02:41.189
Is that true?

02:42.292 --> 02:43.624
Why'd you do that?

02:43.626 --> 02:44.491
She deserved it.

02:44.493 --> 02:45.725
Daphne.

02:45.727 --> 02:47.193
Let's be honest --
the reasons why

02:47.195 --> 02:48.794
Are no longer relevant
to the discussion.

02:48.796 --> 02:51.163
Langhorne academy has
a zero-tolerance policy

02:51.165 --> 02:52.497
When it comes to fighting.

02:52.499 --> 02:54.699
I'm very sorry,
but as of this moment,

02:54.701 --> 02:57.702
Daphne's suspended
for three days.

02:57.704 --> 02:59.270
[ cadence crying ]

02:59.272 --> 03:01.505
Seriously? I've been calling
for four days.

03:01.507 --> 03:03.173
Is juliette even getting
these messages?

03:03.175 --> 03:05.575
Oh! Oh! Oh, hi, baby.
Hey. Hey. Hey.

03:05.577 --> 03:08.144
How can you say you don't know?
You're the tour manager.

03:08.146 --> 03:10.212
You expect me to believe you
haven't talked to her all week?

03:10.214 --> 03:11.246
Hey.

03:11.247 --> 03:12.279
Whoa, whoa. Hey.
There she is.

03:12.282 --> 03:14.215
Good morning, cady.

03:14.217 --> 03:17.251
Hey, for the last time,
her name is cadence, okay?

03:17.253 --> 03:18.352
Yeah, I'll hold.

03:18.353 --> 03:19.452
What's with
all the fussiness?

03:19.455 --> 03:20.554
Talking about avery
or the baby?

03:20.556 --> 03:22.206
Heard that.

03:22.207 --> 03:23.857
Uh...Diaper?
I don't know.

03:23.859 --> 03:25.658
[ sniffs ]
nope. All good.

03:25.660 --> 03:27.292
Yeah, hello? Hello?

03:27.294 --> 03:29.327
Look, if I had
juliette's cell number,

03:29.329 --> 03:30.761
Don't you think
I'd be calling it right now?

03:30.763 --> 03:32.295
Just put her
on the phone!

03:32.297 --> 03:33.696
Dude, hang up. They're not
gonna put you through.

03:33.698 --> 03:35.230
You know,
as much fun as this is,

03:35.232 --> 03:36.898
I think I'm gonna
head on over to kevin's.

03:36.900 --> 03:38.266
Wait. Uh --
hello?

03:38.268 --> 03:39.467
I just made breakfast,
man.
Hello?!

03:39.469 --> 03:40.835
They just hung up on me!

03:40.837 --> 03:42.503
This is --
this is unbelievable.

03:42.505 --> 03:43.704
No, no, no, no.

03:43.706 --> 03:45.238
You need to calm down,

03:45.240 --> 03:46.772
Take a couple
of deep breaths, okay?

03:46.774 --> 03:49.541
[ sighs ] you know what?
I'm gonna go shower, all right?

03:49.543 --> 03:51.843
What about the pancakes?
They're hot. They're fresh.

03:51.845 --> 03:53.244
[ crying ]

03:53.246 --> 03:55.513
Aw.

03:55.514 --> 03:57.781
Why am I the only one
who's ever in a good mood, huh?

04:01.552 --> 04:02.851
Hey.
Hey.

04:02.853 --> 04:04.419
What are you
still doing here?

04:04.421 --> 04:06.187
I thought you would have
gone home for the break.

04:06.189 --> 04:08.355
Well, colt and sage are
on vacation with their mother,

04:08.357 --> 04:10.890
So not much to rush home to
at the moment.

04:10.892 --> 04:12.291
What about you?
You heading home?

04:12.293 --> 04:13.859
Ah, it's just
a couple days off,

04:13.861 --> 04:15.861
And the baby
gets a little cranky

04:15.863 --> 04:17.629
When I come and go
like that, so...

04:17.631 --> 04:19.797
Yeah, I get that.

04:19.799 --> 04:21.331
Well,
I'll see you around.

04:22.634 --> 04:24.433
What are you gonna do?
Just kill some time?

04:24.435 --> 04:26.234
Uh,
I'm just gonna visit

04:26.236 --> 04:28.603
A few of my favorite
indianapolis landmarks.

04:28.605 --> 04:29.970
We'll see ya.

04:32.574 --> 04:33.773
Do you want
some company?

04:35.910 --> 04:38.644
For the most part,
the results are consistent --

04:38.646 --> 04:40.912
Pupils nonresponsive,
no reaction to pain stimulus.

04:40.914 --> 04:43.314
There was a slight gag reflex,
but overall,

04:43.316 --> 04:47.318
Our findings indicate
very few brain-stem reflexes.

04:47.320 --> 04:49.753
I'm sorry, but at this point,
we feel it's appropriate

04:49.755 --> 04:51.888
To readdress
the goals of care.

04:51.890 --> 04:54.523
Readdress the...

04:54.525 --> 04:55.690
What's that
supposed to mean?

04:55.692 --> 04:57.491
Mr. Claybourne,
your sister has suffered

04:57.493 --> 04:58.959
A devastating hemorrhage.

04:58.961 --> 05:01.461
There's very little
brain-stem function left,

05:01.463 --> 05:04.564
Which means that her body
is being kept alive by machines.

05:04.566 --> 05:05.898
And if we remove
those machines,

05:05.900 --> 05:07.432
We believe
she will die within minutes.

05:07.434 --> 05:08.683
All right,
stop right there,

05:08.684 --> 05:09.933
'cause she's been hooked up
to machines before,

05:09.936 --> 05:11.001
And she came back.

05:11.003 --> 05:13.737
I know how difficult
this must be,

05:13.739 --> 05:15.472
But there's nothing more
we can do.

05:15.474 --> 05:17.841
If you choose to keep
your mother on life support --

05:17.843 --> 05:19.475
<i> If?</i> Did you really just --
did you say "if"?

05:19.477 --> 05:22.010
...She'll have to be moved
to a long-term nursing facility.

05:22.012 --> 05:23.978
And even then,
in my professional opinion,

05:23.980 --> 05:25.713
Recovery is not likely.

05:25.714 --> 05:27.447
It's not likely,
but it's not impossible, right?

05:27.450 --> 05:28.582
I mean, can you tell me,

05:28.584 --> 05:29.916
With absolute certainty
over there,

05:29.918 --> 05:31.951
That my sister
won't wake up?
Of course not.

05:31.953 --> 05:33.752
In the medical profession,
nothing's 100%.
Then that's it. No.

05:33.754 --> 05:35.253
We're not taking her
off life support.

05:35.255 --> 05:38.022
Mr. Claybourne,
I appreciate how you feel,

05:38.024 --> 05:40.023
But, respectfully,
it's not up to you.

05:41.626 --> 05:43.626
It's up to ms. O'connor.

05:44.762 --> 05:45.994
Excuse me?

05:45.996 --> 05:47.662
You have
the medical power of attorney

05:47.664 --> 05:49.330
Your mother signed
before the surgery.

05:49.332 --> 05:50.764
It's still in effect.

05:50.766 --> 05:53.800
So the decision is yours
and yours alone.

05:55.804 --> 05:58.871
¶¶

06:05.378 --> 06:07.010
So, what?

06:07.012 --> 06:08.189
You're just saying my opinion
doesn't matter at all here?

06:08.190 --> 06:09.367
Of course it matters.
You're family.

06:09.368 --> 06:10.545
The doctor's just
got to follow the rules

06:10.548 --> 06:11.813
And do things officially.

06:11.815 --> 06:13.948
All right, fine --
officially, then,

06:13.950 --> 06:15.916
Tell him that we're not
taking her off life support.

06:20.521 --> 06:22.387
Scarlett.

06:22.389 --> 06:23.488
Scarlett, no, baby.

06:23.490 --> 06:25.490
Even the doc here
himself --

06:25.491 --> 06:27.491
He admitted that they can't be
100% sure she's gone.

06:27.494 --> 06:28.926
She came back once.
She can do it again, all right?

06:28.928 --> 06:30.928
She just needs some time,
baby.

06:30.930 --> 06:32.462
[ sighs ]
just time.

06:32.464 --> 06:33.896
I-is she in pain?

06:33.898 --> 06:35.564
No, we don't think so.

06:35.566 --> 06:36.765
But just because
there's no pain

06:36.767 --> 06:38.433
Doesn't mean
she's not suffering.

06:38.435 --> 06:40.034
What the hell
does that mean?

06:40.036 --> 06:42.870
It means we could
keep her alive indefinitely,

06:42.872 --> 06:44.638
But the likelihood
of a meaningful recovery

06:44.640 --> 06:46.706
Is very, very low.

06:46.708 --> 06:50.843
However, if you choose to
let your mother go peacefully,

06:50.845 --> 06:53.812
Her death could have tremendous
meaning for so many families.

06:53.814 --> 06:56.748
I-I don't have to tell you the
importance of organ donation.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.049
Okay, look, you need
to back off right now.

06:58.051 --> 06:59.383
No, no, no. Wait.
You understand me?

06:59.385 --> 07:00.751
Just --
you back off.

07:00.753 --> 07:03.053
What if she is<i> not</i> gone?

07:03.055 --> 07:04.821
What if she is
that one in a million?

07:05.990 --> 07:07.756
Perhaps I can help you
better understand

07:07.758 --> 07:09.023
What we're up against.

07:09.025 --> 07:11.091
There's something
called an apnea test.

07:11.093 --> 07:13.827
We would slowly take your mother
off life support

07:13.829 --> 07:15.595
In a controlled environment

07:15.597 --> 07:17.797
And see if she can
take a breath on her own.

07:17.799 --> 07:19.898
It might help you
with the decision.

07:22.702 --> 07:24.101
Let's do it.

07:24.103 --> 07:27.471
Of all the things
I thought might happen today,

07:27.473 --> 07:28.939
You getting kicked out of school
for being in a fistfight

07:28.941 --> 07:30.240
Was not one of them.

07:30.241 --> 07:31.540
You want to tell me
what happened?

07:31.543 --> 07:32.909
No.

07:32.911 --> 07:34.810
Well, that's not gonna be
an acceptable answer.

07:34.812 --> 07:36.845
You are gonna tell me
what happened.

07:36.847 --> 07:38.947
Did she come after you?
Was she harassing you?

07:38.949 --> 07:40.682
Bullying you?
What happened?

07:40.684 --> 07:42.684
Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

07:42.686 --> 07:45.653
We're gonna get through this.
We are.

07:45.655 --> 07:47.854
But you're gonna
have to be honest with me.

07:49.757 --> 07:52.357
She said
dad was a criminal

07:52.359 --> 07:53.991
And that he's going to jail
for a long time.

07:53.993 --> 07:56.493
And I tried to tell her
that he's innocent,

07:56.495 --> 07:58.961
But she wouldn't stop.

08:01.432 --> 08:02.531
[ sniffles ]

08:02.533 --> 08:03.899
I'm sorry, baby.

08:03.901 --> 08:05.600
[ crying ]
why is dad in jail

08:05.602 --> 08:07.702
When he didn't
even do anything wrong?

08:07.704 --> 08:10.137
I just want to see him.

08:10.139 --> 08:11.538
[ sobs ]
I know.

08:11.540 --> 08:14.140
Come on.
Let's go, let's go.

08:14.142 --> 08:15.708
[ cadence crying ]
I'm sorry, guys.

08:15.710 --> 08:16.975
I don't know why
she's so fussy today.

08:16.977 --> 08:18.843
Here. Let me walk her
for a bit.

08:18.845 --> 08:20.377
You don't have to
do that.

08:20.379 --> 08:21.745
Please.
I love cadence.

08:21.746 --> 08:23.112
And since I'm currently
being paid to do nothing,

08:23.115 --> 08:24.747
It's the least I can do.

08:24.749 --> 08:26.048
Wait. You're still
on the payroll?

08:26.050 --> 08:27.382
Do you have
juliette's new number?

08:27.384 --> 08:29.034
Sorry. No.

08:29.035 --> 08:30.685
I haven't seen or spoken to her
since she went on tour.

08:30.687 --> 08:32.687
And yet,
the paychecks still come.

08:32.689 --> 08:34.722
So, seriously, anytime
you need help with cadence,

08:34.724 --> 08:35.723
I'm your girl.

08:35.725 --> 08:37.691
Thanks.
Mm-hmm.

08:37.693 --> 08:38.692
[ crying continues ]
shh, shh, shh.

08:38.694 --> 08:40.026
How you holding up?

08:40.028 --> 08:42.061
Well, let's see, glenn.

08:42.063 --> 08:44.897
I've been abandoned
by my wife twice.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.398
My daughter no longer
has a mother.

08:46.400 --> 08:48.066
How do you<i> think</i>
I'm doing?

08:48.068 --> 08:51.436
Look, I've known juliette longer
than anyone, and believe me --

08:51.438 --> 08:53.070
I've seen her walk away
plenty of times.

08:53.072 --> 08:55.172
Sooner or later,
she always finds her way back.

08:55.174 --> 08:56.673
Right. So what am I
supposed to do?

08:56.675 --> 08:58.908
Just sit by the phone,
hope she calls?

08:58.910 --> 09:00.175
Look, we both know
this isn't her.

09:00.177 --> 09:01.676
She's sick, remember?

09:01.678 --> 09:03.010
You think I haven't tried

09:03.012 --> 09:05.078
A dozen different ways
to help her?

09:05.080 --> 09:06.846
She doesn't want
to get better, glenn.

09:06.848 --> 09:07.913
<i> That's</i> the problem.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.514
Emily:
It's okay, cadence.

09:11.985 --> 09:14.685
Emily, can you watch cadence
for me today?
Sure.

09:14.687 --> 09:16.553
Okay, uh, just take her
back to my place

09:16.555 --> 09:17.887
And wait for me there.

09:17.889 --> 09:18.787
Okay.

09:18.789 --> 09:20.121
What are you gonna do?

09:20.123 --> 09:22.089
[ sighs ]

09:22.091 --> 09:24.424
Something I should have done
two months ago.

09:24.426 --> 09:27.126
Avery, look,
wherever juliette is,

09:27.128 --> 09:29.161
I'm sure she's just as miserable
as you are.

09:29.163 --> 09:30.428
Probably more.

09:30.430 --> 09:32.897
[ engine revs ]

09:44.776 --> 09:48.511
Nice try, danica, but you're
still 45 seconds off my mark.

09:48.513 --> 09:51.013
So, this is really your idea
of a fun day off?

09:51.015 --> 09:54.850
We are standing on america's
original motor speedway,

09:54.852 --> 09:58.019
Home of the indianapolis 500
and the brickyard 400.

09:58.021 --> 09:59.653
What the ryman is
to country music,

09:59.655 --> 10:01.621
This place is to racing.

10:01.623 --> 10:04.490
This is a temple,
and we have come to worship.

10:04.492 --> 10:06.558
And here, I thought we were
just driving around in circles

10:06.560 --> 10:08.860
In a hot car
in front of an empty grandstand.

10:08.862 --> 10:10.127
All right,
forgetting for a moment

10:10.129 --> 10:12.629
The piece of my soul
that just died,

10:12.631 --> 10:13.796
What's<i> your</i> idea of fun?

10:15.733 --> 10:17.199
Juliette: Tequila.

10:17.201 --> 10:18.833
Yes, ma'am.

10:18.835 --> 10:20.801
A bar --
at noon on a weekday.

10:20.803 --> 10:22.536
Not just a bar.
It's a party.

10:22.538 --> 10:24.871
¶ ...All she needs
to put the bite on you ¶

10:24.873 --> 10:27.206
You and I have very different
definitions of the word "party."

10:27.208 --> 10:28.974
Just you wait.

10:28.976 --> 10:31.977
¶ ...Like a copper-headed
queen ¶

10:31.979 --> 10:33.878
[ acoustic guitar playing ]

10:38.116 --> 10:39.715
Hey, will.
Come on in.

10:39.717 --> 10:41.650
I'm sorry. I didn't realize
you were working.

10:41.652 --> 10:43.518
I'll, uh,
I'll leave you be.

10:43.520 --> 10:45.052
No. No, no, no. Stay.
It's just an impromptu thing.

10:45.054 --> 10:47.020
Uh, grab a guitar,
join us.

10:47.022 --> 10:50.223
I-I don't really want
to mess with the chemistry.

10:50.225 --> 10:51.641
Besides, I'm guessing

10:51.642 --> 10:53.058
I'm about the least-experienced
writer in this room.

10:53.061 --> 10:54.460
[ laughter ]

10:54.461 --> 10:55.860
Well, we were
just about to take a break,

10:55.863 --> 10:57.529
So at least stay
for lunch.

10:57.531 --> 10:59.764
I'd love for my friends
to get to know you better.

10:59.766 --> 11:01.966
Yeah, sure.

11:01.968 --> 11:03.867
[ buzzer, lock disengages ]

11:06.705 --> 11:08.571
There's a message
from your lawyer.

11:08.573 --> 11:10.739
You need to call your ex-wife
immediately.

11:10.741 --> 11:11.806
Something about your kids.

11:13.709 --> 11:14.974
Look,
I supported the idea

11:14.976 --> 11:16.942
Of you not seeing the girls
right away,

11:16.944 --> 11:18.710
Because lord knows
I don't love the idea

11:18.712 --> 11:20.144
Of them seeing
their father in jail,

11:20.146 --> 11:22.112
But things have gotten
out of control, teddy.

11:22.114 --> 11:23.614
I need your help here.

11:23.615 --> 11:25.115
And -- and say what?
What am I supposed to tell them?

11:25.117 --> 11:26.950
Tell them the truth, teddy.
Come on!

11:26.952 --> 11:30.019
Rayna, the truth is that
I pled "not guilty," remember?

11:30.021 --> 11:32.287
And my attorney is confident
that I can beat this thing

11:32.289 --> 11:33.638
If we just drag it out
long enough,

11:33.639 --> 11:34.988
Wait -- wait for the public
to lose interest.

11:34.991 --> 11:37.624
Teddy, your daughters
are not gonna lose interest.

11:37.626 --> 11:39.125
They need to see you.

11:39.127 --> 11:42.528
They are being harassed
every single day.

11:42.530 --> 11:44.530
They are asking me,
"why won't our daddy see us?

11:44.532 --> 11:45.697
Does he not love us
anymore?

11:45.699 --> 11:46.898
Is he innocent?
Is he guilty?"

11:46.900 --> 11:48.165
I don't know
what to tell them anymore.

11:48.167 --> 11:50.200
<i> You've</i> got to talk to them.

11:50.201 --> 11:52.234
Okay, I know, I know.
And I'm sorry. I really am.

11:52.237 --> 11:54.770
But if you just can hang on
a little while longer, please.

11:54.772 --> 11:56.805
No, I cannot hang on
for a little bit longer.

11:56.807 --> 11:58.840
They want to see you,
okay?

11:58.842 --> 11:59.941
Noel: I've got to
get the band finalized,

11:59.943 --> 12:01.075
