you still love her.

25:48.198 --> 25:53.200
Why else would you be
so mad at her for so long?

25:53.202 --> 25:55.669
It's 'cause she mattered.

25:55.671 --> 25:57.637
What if I make
the wrong choice?

25:58.806 --> 26:01.740
You're the wisest,
most level-headed,

26:01.742 --> 26:04.242
Empathetic person
I've ever met.

26:04.244 --> 26:08.445
And if you believe
it's the right thing to do...

26:08.447 --> 26:09.679
That's good enough
for me.

26:18.822 --> 26:20.655
I mean, who the hell
does she think she is?

26:20.657 --> 26:22.556
She doesn't know me.

26:22.558 --> 26:24.190
Like it's up to me

26:24.192 --> 26:26.524
To solve country music's problem
with gay artists.

26:29.428 --> 26:30.527
What?
What aren't you saying?

26:31.696 --> 26:32.895
She's not wrong.

26:32.897 --> 26:36.531
You<i> could</i> be an important voice
for the community.

26:36.533 --> 26:37.732
There it is again,
that word -- community.

26:37.734 --> 26:39.700
"the cause," "us," "we."

26:39.702 --> 26:41.452
I didn't sign up for that.

26:41.453 --> 26:43.203
